Articles.Content:

On my old PC it worked fine but now that I reinstalled it on my new PC it's stuck loading.

My KSP version is 1.0.5 build 1028.

Before, on my old PC, my ksp had been stuck on 'FASAApollo.SM.Engine' before. But I have forgotten how I fixed it. I don't think it has to do with FASA, because if I uninstall FASA it gets stuck on a Mechjeb part and if I uninstall that it gets stuck on a ProceduralParts part.

Here is a link to my full output_log.txt

 

Edited December 26, 2015 by xunu

Reinstalling KSP (again) seems to have fixed all the problems

Probably some data got corrupted during installation..

Edited December 26, 2015 by xunu
grammarz
No, the issue was you were on the unpatched version of 1.0.5. Redownloading gave you the patched version (see the Silent Patch thread in the Announcements forum. Apparently too silent.)
